 commitment, bodhicitta, devotion, just really reveling in the preciousness of the moment

00:07:33.840 --> 00:07:39.560
 and sparking with that, with love and devotion for all the lineage, feeling the presence

00:07:39.560 --> 00:07:46.380
 of the three jewels, the three roots, and our trust in the three jewels, doing our lineage

00:07:46.380 --> 00:07:51.620
 prayers, kind of setting that basis of the heart of the practice, and then with nundro

00:07:51.620 --> 00:07:57.400
 in particular, that kind of blends in with the four thoughts that turn the mind toward

00:07:57.400 --> 00:08:10.180
 the Dharma, with refuge, which is essentially affirming our deep trust and joy in the Buddha,

00:08:10.180 --> 00:08:16.840
 in the Buddha's teachings, and all those who uphold them, and in our own, in the innate

00:08:16.840 --> 00:08:23.800
 goodness and beautiful potential of our own mind, and our own experience to be totally

00:08:23.800 --> 00:08:32.440
 free, and that all beings can have that, so generating that really thought of enlightenment

00:08:32.440 --> 00:08:40.240
 for all beings, which is bodhicitta, and then we're generating merit through the third part,

